<!-- Headings -->
<h2 id="headings">
  <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/HTML/Element/Heading_Elements"
    >Headings</a
  >
</h2>
<h1>Heading 1</h1>
<h2>Heading 2</h2>
<h3>Heading 3</h3>
<h4>Heading 4</h4>
<h5>Heading 5</h5>
<h6>Heading 6</h6>

<!-- Text: paragraphs and inline formatting -->
<h2 id="text">
  <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/HTML/Element/p">Text</a>
</h2>
<p>
  This is a paragraph of text. Sometimes you want your text to be
  <strong>strong</strong> and other times you want to put <em>emphasis</em> on it.
  You can also <mark>highlight text</mark> to draw attention to it.
</p>
<p>
  Inline elements include <small>small text</small>, superscript<sup>hi</sup>,
  subscript<sub>bye</sub>,
  <abbr title="abbreviations">abbr</abbr>, and
  <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dfn"
    >defined terms</a
  >
  like <dfn>classless CSS</dfn> — a stylesheet that requires no class attributes.
</p>

<!-- Links -->
<h2 id="links">
  <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/HTML/Element/a">Links</a>
</h2>
<p>
  This is <a href="https://trevortylerlee.com">an inline link</a>. Links can
  also be
  <a href="https://trevortylerlee.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >opened in a new tab</a
  >.
</p>

<!-- Blockquote -->
<h2 id="blockquote">
  <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/HTML/Element/blockquote"
    >Blockquote</a
  >
</h2>
<blockquote>
  <p>
    "In a hole in the ground there lived a hobbit. Not a nasty, dirty, wet hole,
    filled with the end of worms and an oozy smell, nor yet a dry, bare, sandy
    hole with nothing to sit down on or eat: it was a hobbit-hole, and that
    means comfort."
  </p>
  <footer>― J.R.R. Tolkien, <cite>The Hobbit</cite></footer>
</blockquote>

<!-- Lists -->
<h2 id="lists">
  <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/HTML/Element/ul">Lists</a>
</h2>
<h3>Unordered List</h3>
<ul>
  <li>First item</li>
  <li>Second item</li>
  <li>Third item with a <a href="#">link</a></li>
</ul>
<h3>Ordered List</h3>
<ol>
  <li>First item</li>
  <li>Second item</li>
  <li>Third item</li>
</ol>
<h3>Description List</h3>
<dl>
  <dt>HTML</dt>
  <dd>
    The standard markup language for documents designed to be displayed in a web
    browser.
  </dd>
  <dt>CSS</dt>
  <dd>
    A style sheet language used for describing the presentation of a document
    written in HTML.
  </dd>
</dl>

<!-- Table -->
